>anything different between these guys and softlanding.  Perhaps I am
>overlooking something, but I can't see it.

They imply that Linux will run Windows programs.  That is simply not
true (yet).

They do not mention that the DOS Emulator doesn't work for many programs.

They advertise ELF binary compatibility, but I believe that ELF is still
ALPHA software.

They do not mention that Linux is still BETA software.

This ad is misleading at best.

