>     Don't get me wrong, I'm not bashing Linux.  Linux IS my FAVORITE
>   Operating System.  Also I like, and have installed at least 3 of the SLS
>   releases.  BUT, I am VERY WORRIED about ad's like this doing more harm
>   than good.  I honestly believe that this ad misrepresents Linux, and will
>   raise new user's expectations to unrealistic levels.  After actually
>   seeing the release, a lot of these people that thought it would be more
>   than it is, will junk it and never look at it again!
>
>I understand a bit of what you are saying, but I don't really see
>anything different between these guys and softlanding.  Perhaps I am
>overlooking something, but I can't see it.
>
>         Zane in DC
>
>
What kind of bullsh*t is this. Now this article looks like something that is
going to promise a bunch of things that linux can't provide (yet!) and piss
off maybe thousands of people who will respond to this ad and not get what
it advertised. Can't people experience Linux for what it is, a great and free
operating system that has delivered us from the hands of Microsloth, instead of
just looking for a way to make a quick buck.  I don't think we want people
putting this kind of trash in magazines. At least if your going to do something
like this, be honest in the ad about what people are getting, and let them know
all the options, such as getting it free. I'd like to see people take a stand
to uphold the integrity and reputation of what linux has become.
